  "text": "Calorimeter data were extrapolated to 24 h values, based on average minute values. 24-h EE and total substrate oxidation were determined from oxygen consumption (VO 2 ), carbon dioxide production (VCO 2 ), and urinary nitrogen excretion, as previously described [CITATION_1] . Integrated VAS and blood responses during the waking hours (0730-2200) were determined by calculating the integrated area under the curve (AUC) using the trapezoid rule.",
